SIMPLE: grievous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Grievous
<hw>Griev"ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>grevous</ets>, <ets>grevos</ets>, LL. <ets>gravosus</ets>. See
<er>Grief</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Causing grief or sorrow;
painful; afflictive; hard to bear; offensive; harmful.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The famine was <qex>grievous</qex> in the land.</q> <rj><qau>Gen.
xii. 10.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The thing was very <qex>grievous</qex> in Abraham's sight.</q>
<rj><qau>Gen. xxi. 11.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Characterized by great atrocity; heinous;
aggravated; flagitious; <as>as, a <ex>grievous</ex> sin</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Gen. xviii. 20.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Full of, or expressing, grief; showing great sorrow
or affliction; <as>as, a <ex>grievous</ex> cry</as>.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Griev"ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Griev"ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Griff</ent>⟦br⟧
